<p><cite>The Five: the untold lives of the women killed by Jack the Ripper</cite>, by Hallie Rubenhold. Heartbreaking account of the lack of support or sympathy for poor people, especially women, in Victorian Britain, and necessary corrective to popular images of the Ripper and his victims. They were so much more, and he was so much less - 5*</p>

